One individual in eclipse plumage was seen foraging on a small mudflat on the shore of the Bracinho River. We identified this species by its brown upper, white belly and eyebrow, dark beak, and yellowish legs (
<bibRefCitation author="Gwynne JA &amp; Ridgely RS &amp; Tudor G &amp; Argel M" box="[910,1126,1121,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" refId="ref17338" refString="Gwynne JA, Ridgely RS, Tudor G, Argel M (2010) Aves do Brasil: Pantanal &amp; Cerrado. Horizonte, Sao Paulo, 322 pp." type="book" year="2010">Gwynne et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). We saw discreet spots on the belly, indicating its non-breeding status.
</paragraph>
